        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 11:45PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 1143 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking slow-moving thunderstorms
across the area, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Minor flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Slowing or redirecting of traffic due to ponding or flowing
water. Closure of waterfront access due to flooding.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Madison, Keokuk, Carthage, Nauvoo, Hamilton, Warsaw, West Point,
Donnellson, Montrose, Wayland, Alexandria, Ferris, Franklin, Colusa,
Adrian, New Boston, Pilot Grove, Burnside, Niota, and St.
Francisville.

Rainfall amounts of 1 to 2 inches have fallen in some locations
within the heavier rain.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is occurring and may lead to localized flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. Stay away from
flooded areas. Report any flooding to local law enforcement.

If the heavy rain continues, a flash flood warning may be needed.</instruction>
